The paper focuses on developing a data-driven grasp synthesis method for robotic hands, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a deep neural network architecture, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The model is trained on a large dataset, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) methods. The paper also discusses the successful grasps achieved in real-world experiments, which involves system and control (cs.SY) aspects.
